Level 1 Practice: Defining and Using Macro Variables for Substitution


1.Reminder: If you restarted your SAS session, you must submit the libname.sas program in the EMC1V2 folder to access your practice files
1.注意事項 SASセッションを再起動した場合、練習用ファイルにアクセスするためには、EMC1V2フォルダー内のlibname.sasプログラムを提出する必要があります。

Open the m102p01.sas program from the practices folder. Submit the program and review the log and output. 
practices フォルダにある m102p01.sas プログラムを開いてください。プログラムをサブミットし、ログと出力を確認します。

Verify that the title is US Customers Ages 18 to 24 and that 127 rows were read.

Create a macro variable named Country and assign the value US. Replace all occurrences of US with references 
to the macro variable Country. Submit the program and verify that the results are the same as step 1.
国という名前のマクロ変数を作成し、USという値を代入します。USというマクロ変数の出現箇所をすべて 
マクロ変数Countryへの参照に置き換える。プログラムを送信し、結果がステップ1と同じであることを確認する。

Modify the value of the macro variable Country to FR. Resubmit the program.
マクロ変数Countryの値をFRに変更する。プログラムを再送信します。

How many rows were read? Enter a numeric value.
46

正解
46 rows have Country = "FR"

%let Country=FR;
title "&Country Customers Ages 18 to 24";
proc print data=mc1.customers;
    var Name Age Type;
    where Country = "&Country" 
          and Age between 18 and 24;
run;
title;



2.Modify the program as follows:

Create additional macro variables, Age1 and Age2.

Set Age1 to 25, Age2 to 34, and Country to AU.

Replace all occurrences of 18 and 24 with references to Age1 and Age2.

Submit the program.

What is the report title?

MyAnswer:
US Customers Ages Age1 to Age2

正解
%let Country=AU;
%let age1=25;
%let age2=34;
title "&Country Customers Ages &age1 to &age2";
proc print data=mc1.customers;
    var Name Age Type;
    where Country = "&Country" 
          and Age between &age1 and &age2;
run;
title;

The title is AU Customers Ages 25 to 34.

3.How many rows were read?

Note: Enter a numeric value for  your answer.

10
正解
Ten rows were read. 


%let Country=AU;
%let age1=25;
%let age2=34;
title "&Country Customers Ages &age1 to &age2";
proc print data=mc1.customers;
    var Name Age Type;
    where Country = "&Country" 
          and Age between &age1 and &age2;
run;
title;




